item.title: Vic woman lied at border: police
item.description: A Victorian woman has been charged after she allegedly gave false information to police upon her arrival into Queensland.

item.title: Woman charged over puppy scams
item.description: A woman has been charged by Victoria Police over an alleged scam in which she advertised puppies for sale and then disappeared once dog lovers paid her a substantial deposit.

item.title: Infections at Melbourne tower could grow
item.description: An outbreak among construction workers at a Melbourne high-rise tower is expected to grow, with more than 600 employees ordered off site after a dozen became infected.

item.title: Cops stood down over drug probe
item.description: Two Queensland police officers have been stood down as investigations continue into their role in alleged drug trafficking.

item.title: Pets left stranded abroad
item.description: Getting home during a pandemic is hard enough for humans living abroad, but even more challenging if you have four legs and fur.

item.title: Second virus case in NT
item.description: The Northern Territory has confirmed a second case of COVID-19 in as many days after a family returned to Darwin from Melbourne.

item.title: Truck stowaway attempt at Qld border
item.description: Two people who allegedly attempted to enter Queensland stowed away in the back of a truck are set to be charged.

item.title: Sydney virus clusters grow larger
item.description: Seventeen new cases of COVID-19 have been recorded in New South Wales overnight, three of which are returned travellers in hotel quarantine, Dr Jeremy McAnulty confirmed.

item.title: Officer punched at Victorian border: police
item.description: A man wanted on seven outstanding warrants allegedly assaulted a senior police officer after trying to evade a NSW-Victorian border checkpoint on Saturday morning.
